path: ./Audit_Reports_2024/Techrate/Baby Moon Floki Full Smart Contract Security Audit.pdf

findings.title: Owner privileges (In the period when the owner is not renounced)
findings.description: The contract owner has excessive privileges even after ownership renouncement, allowing them to withdraw tokens and BNBs, change fees, and perform other critical actions.

findings.title: Unprotected functions: setFeeTo, setFeeToSetter
findings.description: The functions setFeeTo and setFeeToSetter are unprotected, allowing unauthorized access and potential manipulation of fee settings.

findings.title: Unprotected functions
findings.description: The contract has unprotected functions that can be accessed by anyone, potentially leading to unauthorized state changes or asset manipulation.

findings.title: Unprotected functions
findings.description: The functions factory, WETH, addLiquidity, addLiquidityETH, removeLiquidity, removeLiquidityETH, removeLiquidityWithPermit, removeLiquidityETHWithPermit, swapExactTokensForTokens, swapTokensForExactTokens, swapExactETHForTokens, and swapTokensForExactETH are unprotected.
